name: proteomics
title: Proteomics
summary: Training material for proteomics workflows in Galaxy

subtopics.title: Introduction
subtopics.description: Start here if you are new to proteomic analysis in Galaxy.

subtopics.title: Protein identification and quantification
subtopics.description: These tutorials cover protein identification and/or label-free and label based quantification from data dependent acquisition (DDA) and data independent acquisition (DIA).

subtopics.title: Postprocessing of proteomics data
subtopics.description: These tutorial cover statistical analyses and visualizations after protein identification and quantification.

subtopics.title: Special proteomics techniques
subtopics.description: These tutorials focus on special techniques such as N-terminomics and mass spectrometry imaging.

subtopics.title: Multi-omics analyses
subtopics.description: These tutorials combine proteomics with other -omics technologies such as transcriptomics.

subtopics.title: Prediction of peptide properties
subtopics.description: These tutorials explain in-silico analyses of different peptide properties.

subtopics.title: Metaproteomics analysis of clinical data
subtopics.description: These tutorials are step by step analysis from database generation to the discovery of peptides to verification, quantitation, and interpretation of the results.

references.authors: Kumar D, Yadav AK and Dash D
references.title: Choosing an Optimal Database for Protein Identification from Tandem Mass Spectrometry Data.
Shedding light on black boxes in protein identification.
references.summary: An extensive tutorial for peptide and protein identification, available at http://compomics.com/bioinformatics-for-proteomics. The material is completely based on freely available and open-source tools.

references.title: Current challenges in software solutions for mass spectrometry-based quantitative proteomics
references.summary: A comprehensive review of current quantitative techniques, their advantages and pitfalls.

references.title: Limited and Degradative Proteolysis in the Context of Posttranslational Regulatory Networks: Current Technical and Conceptional Advances
references.summary: Review on LC-MS/MS based proteomic methods to identify neo-N-termini, e.g. generated by protease cleavage.
